The paper deals with the construction of data structures for representing static functions and minimal perfect hash functions using random linear systems on finite fields. This involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
